p style=\"color: #3a3637;\">The most important option is the <strong>Tabs source</strong> - this option specifies the sidebar used as the data source of the widget. When Tabs plugin is active three special widget areas are created – GK Tab I, GK Tab II and GK Tab III – these widget areas don’t exist on the theme and they can be used in the GK Tabs widget to avoid problems with the duplicated widgets.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #3a3637;\">To create tabs, a user must drag some widgets to the specified in the GK Tabs widget sidebar. The titles of these widgets will be used as the tabs titles, the order of the widgets in the sidebar is also important – it will be used in the GK Tabs widget.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #3a3637;\">So, for example, in order to achieve the GK Tabs widget layout as in the first screenshot, you have to put the widgets on the GK Tab I sidebar as following:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #3a3637;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/tabs3-1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2221\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/tabs3-1.jpg\" alt=\"tabs3-1\" width=\"299\" height=\"260\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #3a3637;\"></p>\r\nThe other options are strictly connected with the widget interface:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>First tab </strong>- it specifies the first tab displayed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tabs activator event</strong> - it specifies the event used to activate the tab – it can be a hover or a click event.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Swipe gesture </strong>- you can enable/disable swipe on touchable devices</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Navigation buttons </strong>- you can enabe/disable navigation buttons</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tabs position </strong>- tabs can be placed at the top or bottom of the widget</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Auto animation</strong> - the GK Tabs widget can autoanimate the tabs when this option is enabled. Then, the time between tabs animations is defined in the animation interval option.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Animation speed</strong> - time of the transition between the tabs – defined in miliseconds.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Animation interval</strong> - time for the autoanimation option – defined in miliseconds</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Animation type </strong>- you can select type of animation, like opacity, scale up, scale down, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[info]<span style=\"color: #383637;\">You can download the latest version of this widget from our </span><a style=\"color: #1dbaf4;\" title=\"GK Tabs widget\" href=\"https://github.com/GavickPro/GK-Tabs\">official repository.</a><span style=\"color: #383637;\"> </span>[/info]','GK Tabs','','inherit','open','open','','2216-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:20:58','2014-06-17 21:20:58','',2216,'{$page_url}/2216-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2223,1,'2014-06-17 21:22:08','2014-06-17 21:22:08','GK News Show Pro is a complex and powerful widget used for displaying posts with thumbnails and additional content like title, text and additional information.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/gk_nsp_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2214\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/gk_nsp_screen.png\" alt=\"gk_nsp_screen\" width=\"1302\" height=\"530\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFull documentation of this widget can be found <a title=\"GK News Show Pro documentation\" href=\"https://github.com/GavickPro/GK-News-Show-Pro/wiki\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nOn the homepage are used additional GK NSP style: <strong>darkbar</strong>, please check <a title=\"Widget Styles\" href=\"{$page_url}/widget-styles/\">Widget Styles</a> page to get more informations.\r\n\r\n[info]<span style=\"color: #383637;\">You can download the latest version of this widget from our </span><a style=\"color: #1dbaf4;\" title=\"GK Tabs widget\" href=\"https://github.com/GavickPro/GK-News-Show-Pro\">official repository.</a><span style=\"color: #383637;\"> </span>[/info]','GK News Show Pro','','inherit','open','open','','765-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:22:08','2014-06-17 21:22:08','',765,'{$page_url}/765-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2226,1,'2014-06-17 21:26:25','2014-06-17 21:26:25','<span style=\"color: #888888;\">BP Latest Photos is used to display photos from rtMedia plugin for BuddyPress:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/latest_photos_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2225\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/latest_photos_screen.png\" alt=\"latest_photos_screen\" width=\"207\" height=\"138\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">Configuration of this widget is easy and shouldn’t be troublesome.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','BP Latest Photos','','inherit','open','open','','2224-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:26:25','2014-06-17 21:26:25','',2224,'{$page_url}/2224-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2227,1,'2014-06-17 21:26:40','2014-06-17 21:26:40','','gk_latest_photo_configuration','','inherit','open','open','','gk_latest_photo_configuration','','','2014-06-17 21:26:40','2014-06-17 21:26:40','',2224,'{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_latest_photo_configuration.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2228,1,'2014-06-17 21:27:02','2014-06-17 21:27:02','<span style=\"color: #888888;\">BP Latest Photos is used to display photos from rtMedia plugin for BuddyPress:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/latest_photos_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2225\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/latest_photos_screen.png\" alt=\"latest_photos_screen\" width=\"207\" height=\"138\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">Configuration of this widget is easy and shouldn’t be troublesome.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_latest_photo_configuration.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2227\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_latest_photo_configuration.jpg\" alt=\"gk_latest_photo_configuration\" width=\"252\" height=\"283\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"color: #888888;\">By default, widget displays latest photos from all users. When you specify <strong>User ID</strong> option, only photos from specified user will be displayed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #888888;\">Options <strong>Columns and Rows </strong>define amounts of photo’s columns and rows.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #888888;\"><strong>Offset </strong>option allows to select second, third, fourth etc. status from the feeds.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #888888;\">The <strong>cache time</strong> option specifies how often the widget content is generated – it is safe to set it for at least 30-60 minutes or even more if the page isn’t often updated.</p>','BP Latest Photos','','inherit','open','open','','2224-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:27:02','2014-06-17 21:27:02','',2224,'{$page_url}/2224-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2229,1,'2014-06-17 21:28:12','2014-06-17 21:28:12','<span style=\"color: #666666;\">GK Tweets is a simple widget used to display latest tweets for specific query:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2236\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_screen\" width=\"1254\" height=\"295\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">The widget have a few important options:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2237\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_config\" width=\"442\" height=\"706\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">First three options are used to specify the query phrase, amount of tweets to load and the result type.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">Rest of the options is connected with the widget layout. You can enable or disable showing of the following elements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"color: #666666;\">\r\n	<li>user avatar</li>\r\n	<li>tweet date</li>\r\n	<li>tweet links (favorite, reply and retweet).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">Please remember that the widget caches the downloaded data and refresh it in every 10 minutes automatically (or on the widget settings save). This mechanism is necessary due Twitter API limits.</p>','GK Tweets','','publish','open','open','','gk-tweets','','','2014-06-17 21:36:09','2014-06-17 21:36:09','',756,'{$page_url}/?page_id=2229',0,'page','',0),(2230,1,'2014-06-17 21:28:12','2014-06-17 21:28:12','todo','GK Tweets','','inherit','open','open','','2229-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:28:12','2014-06-17 21:28:12','',2229,'{$page_url}/2229-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2231,1,'2014-06-17 21:28:28','2014-06-17 21:28:28','<p style=\"color: #555555;\">GK Image Show widget is a simple widget which can be used to create awesome header.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_scree.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2291\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_scree.png\" alt=\"image_show_scree\" width=\"964\" height=\"651\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The slide images are configured in the Media library:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_screen2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2294\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_screen2.png\" alt=\"image_show_screen2\" width=\"794\" height=\"155\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Every slide have few important elements:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_image_show_scrren3-2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2295\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_image_show_scrren3-2.png\" alt=\"gk_image_show_scrren3 2\" width=\"527\" height=\"773\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The title (*)  is used to identify the slide but we will describe it later. In general we recommend to use a simple name like “slideX” where X is a number of the slide. Other marked elements are also important:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">1. The “Caption” is used to generate slide title</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">2. The “Alternative Text” is used to store the slide URL – where the slide is linking,</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">2. The “Description” is used to generate slide subtitle.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">When you have the slides, you can go to the widget settings:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_image_show_conf.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2296\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_image_show_conf.png\" alt=\"gk_image_show_conf\" width=\"436\" height=\"644\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The widget configuration is very easy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">First of all, you have to specify slides used– you have to put media titles separated with a comma – as you can see we have named our slides as “slide_1″,“slide_2″.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Next options are connected with slider width and height on desktop, tablets and mobile devices.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The “Pagination” option enables the pagination on the bottom of the slider.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Next three options are strictly connected with the animation speed (speed of the slides transition), interval (time between two slides) and autoanimation (if you need to autoanimate your slides).</p>','GK ImageShow','','publish','open','open','','gk-imageshow','','','2014-06-22 21:08:22','2014-06-22 21:08:22','',756,'{$page_url}/?page_id=2231',0,'page','',0),(2294,1,'2014-06-22 21:06:13','2014-06-22 21:06:13','','image_show_screen2','','inherit','open','open','','image_show_screen2','','','2014-06-22 21:06:13','2014-06-22 21:06:13','',2231,'{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_screen2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2233,1,'2014-06-17 21:28:55','2014-06-17 21:28:55','<span style=\"color: #888888;\">GK BuddyPress Gallery is used to display photos from rtMedia plugin with the status and (optional) author name and read more link:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/GK_BP_gallery.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2299\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/GK_BP_gallery.png\" alt=\"GK_BP_gallery\" width=\"1240\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">Configuration of this widget is easy and shouldn’t be troublesome.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_buddypress_gallery_conf.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2300\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_buddypress_gallery_conf.png\" alt=\"gk_buddypress_gallery_conf\" width=\"414\" height=\"608\" /></a>\r\n\r\nBy default, widget displays latest photos from all users. When you specify User ID option and select <strong>specific user photos </strong>as a data source, only photos from specified user will be displayed.\r\n\r\n<strong>Offset</strong> option allows to select second, third, fourth etc. status from the feeds.\r\n\r\nNext options are used to specify amount of displayed photos with statuses, show/hide username, readmore button and toggle the widget animation.\r\n\r\nLast option is used to specify the single photo width.','GK BuddyPress Gallery','','publish','open','open','','gk-buddypress-gallery','','','2014-06-22 21:19:11','2014-06-22 21:19:11','',756,'{$page_url}/?page_id=2233',0,'page','',0),(2234,1,'2014-06-17 21:28:55','2014-06-17 21:28:55','todo','GK BuddyPress Gallery','','inherit','open','open','','2233-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:28:55','2014-06-17 21:28:55','',2233,'{$page_url}/2233-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2235,1,'2014-06-17 21:35:19','2014-06-17 21:35:19','<span style=\"color: #666666;\">GK Tweets is a simple widget used to display latest tweets for specific query:</span>\n\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2236\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_screen\" width=\"1254\" height=\"295\" /></a>\n\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">The widget have a few important options:</span>\n\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2237\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_config\" width=\"442\" height=\"706\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;','GK Tweets','','inherit','open','open','','2229-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:35:19','2014-06-17 21:35:19','',2229,'{$page_url}/2229-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2236,1,'2014-06-17 21:31:56','2014-06-17 21:31:56','','gk_tweets_screen','','inherit','open','open','','gk_tweets_screen','','','2014-06-17 21:31:56','2014-06-17 21:31:56','',2229,'{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2237,1,'2014-06-17 21:35:09','2014-06-17 21:35:09','','gk_tweets_config','','inherit','open','open','','gk_tweets_config','','','2014-06-17 21:35:09','2014-06-17 21:35:09','',2229,'{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2238,1,'2014-06-17 21:36:09','2014-06-17 21:36:09','<span style=\"color: #666666;\">GK Tweets is a simple widget used to display latest tweets for specific query:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2236\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_screen.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_screen\" width=\"1254\" height=\"295\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">The widget have a few important options:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2237\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_tweets_config.png\" alt=\"gk_tweets_config\" width=\"442\" height=\"706\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">First three options are used to specify the query phrase, amount of tweets to load and the result type.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">Rest of the options is connected with the widget layout. You can enable or disable showing of the following elements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"color: #666666;\">\r\n	<li>user avatar</li>\r\n	<li>tweet date</li>\r\n	<li>tweet links (favorite, reply and retweet).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"color: #666666;\">Please remember that the widget caches the downloaded data and refresh it in every 10 minutes automatically (or on the widget settings save). This mechanism is necessary due Twitter API limits.</p>','GK Tweets','','inherit','open','open','','2229-revision-v1','','','2014-06-17 21:36:09','2014-06-17 21:36:09','',2229,'{$page_url}/2229-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2293,1,'2014-06-22 21:06:01','2014-06-22 21:06:01','<p style=\"color: #555555;\">GK Image Show widget is a simple widget which can be used to create awesome header.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_scree.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2291\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/image_show_scree.png\" alt=\"image_show_scree\" width=\"964\" height=\"651\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The slide images are configured in the Media library:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Every slide have few important elements:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a style=\"color: #d82731;\" href=\"http://project.gavick.com/dziudek/wordpress/game/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/gk_image_show_screen3.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1602\" src=\"http://project.gavick.com/dziudek/wordpress/game/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/gk_image_show_screen3.png\" alt=\"gk_image_show_screen3\" width=\"569\" height=\"776\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The title (*)  is used to identify the slide but we will describe it later. In general we recommend to use a simple name like “slideX” where X is a number of the slide. Other marked elements are also important:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">1. The “Caption” is used to generate slide title</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">2. The “Alternative Text” is used to store the slide URL – where the slide is linking,</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">2. The “Description” is used to generate slide subtitle.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">When you have the slides, you can go to the widget settings:</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\"><a style=\"color: #d82731;\" href=\"http://project.gavick.com/dziudek/wordpress/game/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/gk_image_show_configuration.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1603\" src=\"http://project.gavick.com/dziudek/wordpress/game/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/gk_image_show_configuration.png\" alt=\"gk_image_show_configuration\" width=\"386\" height=\"799\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The widget configuration is very easy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">First of all, you have to specify slides used– you have to put media titles separated with a comma – as you can see we have named our slides as “slide_1″,“slide_2″.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Next options are connected with slider width and height on desktop, tablets and mobile devices, you can also specify different margin bottom values.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">The “Pagination” option enables the pagination on the bottom of the slider.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #555555;\">Next three options are strictly connected with the animation speed (speed of the slides transition), interval (time between two slides) and autoanimation (if you need to autoanimate your slides).</p>','GK ImageShow','','inherit','open','open','','2231-revision-v1','','','2014-06-22 21:06:01','2014-06-22 21:06:01','',2231,'{$page_url}/2231-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2298,1,'2014-06-22 21:18:27','2014-06-22 21:18:27','<span style=\"color: #888888;\">GK BuddyPress Gallery is used to display photos from rtMedia plugin with the status and (optional) author name and read more link:</span>\n\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/GK_BP_gallery.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2299\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/GK_BP_gallery.png\" alt=\"GK_BP_gallery\" width=\"1240\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">Configuration of this widget is easy and shouldn’t be troublesome.</span>\n\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_buddypress_gallery_conf.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2300\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/gk_buddypress_gallery_conf.png\" alt=\"gk_buddypress_gallery_conf\" width=\"414\" height=\"608\" /></a>\n\nBy default, widget displays latest photos from all users. When you specify User ID option and select <strong>specific user photos </strong>as a data source, only photos from specified user will be displayed.\n\n<strong>Offset</strong> option allows to select second, third, fourth etc. status from the feeds.\n\nNext options are used to specify amount of displayed photos with statuses, show/hide username, readmore button and toggle the','GK BuddyPress Gallery','','inherit','open','open','','2233-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-22 21:18:27','2014-06-22 21:18:27','',2233,'{$page_url}/2233-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2299,1,'2014-06-22 21:12:49','2014-06-22 21:12:49','','GK_BP_gallery','','inherit','open','open','','gk_bp_gallery','','','2014-06-22 21:12:49','2014-06-22 21:12:49','',2233,'{$page_url}/wp-content/upload